<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1399,2000]" pageId="7" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,319,1904,1928]" pageId="7" pageNumber="61">Remarks:</emphasis>
The natural larval food plant of 
<taxonomicName box="[698,810,1905,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Pareronia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[698,810,1905,1928]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="61">Pareronia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
butterflies is 
<taxonomicName box="[971,1075,1904,1927]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Capparaceae" genus="Capparis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Capparales" pageId="7" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[971,1075,1904,1927]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="61">Capparis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1091,1259,1904,1928]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Capparaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Capparales" pageId="7" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Capparidaceae</taxonomicName>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Kunte" box="[1276,1431,1904,1928]" pageId="7" pageNumber="61" refString="Kunte, K. (2000) Butterflies of Peninsular India. Universities Press (India) Limited, Hyderabad and Indian Academy of Sciences, Bangalore, xviii, 254 pp." type="book" year="2000">
Kunte (
<number box="[1362,1423,1904,1928]" pageId="7" pageNumber="61" value="2000.0">2000</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, but the pupa was found hanging on a 
<taxonomicName box="[575,699,1940,1964]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Vitex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="negundo">
<emphasis box="[575,699,1940,1964]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="61">V. negundo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
plant. There is a possibility that larva, in search of food has travelled some distance and pupated on a different species of plant.
</paragraph>
